<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 11:32PM CDT  by NWS Hastings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Greeley,
eastern Valley, northern Sherman and northwestern Howard Counties
through MIDNIGHT CDT...
At 1131 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sherman Reservoir Dam, or 19 miles south of Ord, moving north at 45
mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Scotia and North Loup around 1150 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
central Nebraska.</instruction>
